revisions.description: Added rlHostParamType, rlHostParamUINT, rlHostParamOctetString, rlHostParamIpAddress and rlHostParamObjectId.
Editorial changes to support new MIB compilers.

rsHighPriority.name: rsHighPriority
rsHighPriority.description: This variable indicates the time interval the forwarding task inside the RS works in High Priority Mode.

rsLowPriority.name: rsLowPriority
rsLowPriority.description: This variable indicates the time interval the forwarding task inside the RS works in Low Priority Mode.

rsDbgLevel.name: rsDbgLevel
rsDbgLevel.description: This variable indicates the debug level the Router Server works. the range of this variable is 1..100

rsDiagnosticsEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rsDiagnosticsRequestId.name: rsDiagnosticsRequestId
rsDiagnosticsRequestId.description: The request id of the rejected SNMP request whose diagnostics are specified by this entry. If request id 0xFFFFFFFF is given, the diagnostic of the last rejected SNMP request sent by the querying NMS is returned.

rsDiagnosticsCode.name: rsDiagnosticsCode
rsDiagnosticsCode.description: The code of the rejected the SNMP request whose diagnostics are specified by this entry. This code may be used to find out the reason for rejection if the diagnostic text is unavailable.

rsDiagnosticsLocation.name: rsDiagnosticsLocation
rsDiagnosticsLocation.description: The internal location in the SW rejecting the SNMP request whose diagnostics are specified by this entry. This information is available for debugging purposes only and will be returned in GET requests only if rsDbgLevel >= 99.

rsDiagnosticsText.name: rsDiagnosticsText
rsDiagnosticsText.description: The diagnostic text of the rejected SNMP request whose diagnostics are specified by this entry.
